## Proposed Changes

### 1. Database Schema

#### [MODIFY] [mentor-content.ts](file:///c:/Users/Admin/young-minds-landing-page/lib/db/schema/mentor-content.ts)

**1a. Expand `content_status` enum** — add 3 new values:

```diff
 export const contentStatusEnum = pgEnum('content_status', [
   'DRAFT',
+  'PENDING_REVIEW',
+  'APPROVED',
+  'REJECTED',
-  'PUBLISHED',
   'ARCHIVED'
 ]);
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Migration**: All existing `PUBLISHED` rows will be migrated to `APPROVED` via `UPDATE mentor_content SET status = 'APPROVED' WHERE status = 'PUBLISHED'`. Then the `PUBLISHED` value will be removed from the enum. This is a one-way migration.

**1b. Add review fields to `mentor_content` table**:

```typescript
// New columns on mentor_content
submittedForReviewAt: timestamp('submitted_for_review_at'),  // when mentor clicked "Submit"
reviewedAt: timestamp('reviewed_at'),                         // when admin approved/rejected
reviewedBy: uuid('reviewed_by').references(() => user.id),    // admin user ID
reviewNote: text('review_note'),                              // admin's reason (especially for rejection)
statusBeforeArchive: text('status_before_archive'),           // stores status before archiving (to support restore)
requireReviewAfterRestore: boolean('require_review_after_restore').default(false),
  // If false (default): restoring ARCHIVED content that was previously APPROVED
  //   goes back to APPROVED without re-review.
  // If true: restoring always goes to DRAFT, forcing re-submission.
  // This is a system-level flag that can be changed later via admin settings.
```

**1c. New table: `content_review_audit`** — immutable audit log of every review action:

```typescript
export const contentReviewAudit = pgTable('content_review_audit', {
  id: uuid('id').primaryKey().defaultRandom(),
  contentId: uuid('content_id').references(() => mentorContent.id, { onDelete: 'cascade' }).notNull(),
  mentorId: uuid('mentor_id').references(() => mentors.id, { onDelete: 'cascade' }).notNull(),
  action: text('action').notNull(),       // 'SUBMITTED' | 'APPROVED' | 'REJECTED' | 'RESUBMITTED'
  previousStatus: text('previous_status'),
  newStatus: text('new_status').notNull(),
  reviewedBy: uuid('reviewed_by'),        // null for mentor-initiated actions (submit)
  note: text('note'),                     // admin comment / rejection reason
  createdAt: timestamp('created_at').defaultNow().notNull(),
});
```

**1d. New table: `mentor_profile_content`** — which approved content a mentor has chosen to show on their profile:

```typescript
export const mentorProfileContent = pgTable('mentor_profile_content', {
  id: uuid('id').primaryKey().defaultRandom(),
  mentorId: uuid('mentor_id').references(() => mentors.id, { onDelete: 'cascade' }).notNull(),
  contentId: uuid('content_id').references(() => mentorContent.id, { onDelete: 'cascade' }).notNull(),
  displayOrder: integer('display_order').notNull().default(0),
  addedAt: timestamp('added_at').defaultNow().notNull(),
}, (table) => ({
  uniqueMentorContent: unique().on(table.mentorId, table.contentId), // prevent duplicates
}));
```

